When using the default left hand navigation them, and go to administer a space's permissions, the page is too large to fit within a 1024 x 768 screen - causing the page to span out to the right hand side and inducing a horizontal scroll bar within the browser.

We should ensure that all pages render successfully within the 1024 x 768 standard when using our default themes (obviously we can't allow for all themes).

Now that themes are selected during space creation, this is becoming more important.

